musicdiff.visualization 

   1# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   2# Purpose:       visualization is a diff visualization package for use by musicdiff.
   3#                musicdiff is a package for comparing music scores using music21.
   4#
   5# Authors:       Greg Chapman <gregc@mac.com>
   6#                musicdiff is derived from:
   7#                   https://github.com/fosfrancesco/music-score-diff.git
   8#                   by Francesco Foscarin <foscarin.francesco@gmail.com>
   9#
  10# Copyright:     (c) 2022-2024 Francesco Foscarin, Greg Chapman
  11# License:       MIT, see LICENSE
  12# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  13
  14__docformat__ = "google"
  15
  16from pathlib import Path
  17import sys
  18import re
  19import typing as t
  20from fractions import Fraction
  21
  22import music21 as m21
  23from music21.common import OffsetQL, opFrac
  24
  25from musicdiff.annotation import AnnMeasure, AnnVoice, AnnNote
  26from musicdiff.annotation import AnnExtra, AnnLyric, AnnStaffGroup, AnnMetadataItem
  27from musicdiff import M21Utils
  28
  29
  30class Visualization:
  31    # These can be set by the client to different colors
  32    INSERTED_COLOR = "red"
  33    """
  34    `INSERTED_COLOR` can be set to customize the rendered score markup that `mark_diffs` does.
  35    """
  36    DELETED_COLOR = "red"
  37    """
  38    `DELETED_COLOR` can be set to customize the rendered score markup that `mark_diffs` does.
  39    """
  40    CHANGED_COLOR = "red"
  41    """
  42    `CHANGED_COLOR` can be set to customize the rendered score markup that `mark_diffs` does.
  43    """
  44
  45    @staticmethod
  46    def mark_diffs(
  47        score1: m21.stream.Score,
  48        score2: m21.stream.Score,
  49        operations: list[tuple]
  50    ) -> None:
  51        """
  52        Mark up two music21 scores with the differences described by an operations
  53        list (e.g. a list returned from `musicdiff.Comparison.annotated_scores_diff`).
  54
  55        Args:
  56            score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score to mark up
  57            score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score to mark up
  58            operations (list[tuple]): The operations list that describes the difference
  59                between the two scores
  60        """
  61        changedStr: str
  62        for op in operations:
  63            # bar
  64            if op[0] == "insbar":
  65                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMeasure)
  66                # color all the notes in the inserted score2 measure
  67                # using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  68                measure2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].measure)  # type: ignore
  69                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
  70                    assert measure2 is not None
  71                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted measure")
  72                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  73                measure2.insert(0, textExp)
  74                measure2.style.color = (
  75                    Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  76                )  # this apparently does nothing
  77                for el in measure2.recurse().notesAndRests:
  78                    el.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  79                continue
  80
  81            if op[0] == "delbar":
  82                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMeasure)
  83                # color all the notes in the deleted score1 measure
  84                # using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  85                measure1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].measure)  # type: ignore
  86                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
  87                    assert measure1 is not None
  88                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted measure")
  89                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  90                measure1.insert(0, textExp)
  91                measure1.style.color = (
  92                    Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  93                )  # this apparently does nothing
  94                for el in measure1.recurse().notesAndRests:
  95                    el.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  96                continue
  97
  98            # voices
  99            if op[0] == "voiceins":
 100                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnVoice)
 101                # color all the notes in the inserted score2 voice
 102                # using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 103                voice2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].voice)  # type: ignore
 104                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 105                    assert voice2 is not None
 106                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted voice")
 107                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 108                voice2.insert(0, textExp)
 109
 110                voice2.style.color = (
 111                    Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 112                )  # this apparently does nothing
 113                for el in voice2.recurse().notesAndRests:
 114                    el.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 115                continue
 116
 117            if op[0] == "voicedel":
 118                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnVoice)
 119                # color all the notes in the deleted score1 voice
 120                # using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 121                voice1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].voice)  # type: ignore
 122                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 123                    assert voice1 is not None
 124                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted voice")
 125                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 126                voice1.insert(0, textExp)
 127
 128                voice1.style.color = (
 129                    Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 130                )  # this apparently does nothing
 131                for el in voice1.recurse().notesAndRests:
 132                    el.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 133                continue
 134
 135            # extra
 136            if op[0] == "extrains":
 137                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 138                # color the extra using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR,
 139                # and add a textExpression describing the insertion.
 140                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 141                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 142                    assert extra2 is not None
 143                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"inserted {extra2.classes[0]}")
 144                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 145                if isinstance(extra2, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 146                    insertionPoint = extra2.getFirst()
 147                    if isinstance(insertionPoint, m21.stream.Measure):
 148                        # insertionPoint is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 149                        # inside the measure
 150                        insertionPoint.insert(0, textExp)
 151                    else:
 152                        # insertionPoint is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 153                        insertionPoint.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint.offset, textExp)
 154                else:
 155                    # extra2 is not a spanner, put the textExp right next to it
 156                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp)
 157                continue
 158
 159            if op[0] == "extradel":
 160                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 161                # color the extra using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 162                # describing the deletion.
 163                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 164                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 165                    assert extra1 is not None
 166                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"deleted {extra1.classes[0]}")
 167                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 168                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 169                    insertionPoint = extra1.getFirst()
 170                    if isinstance(insertionPoint, m21.stream.Measure):
 171                        # insertionPoint is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 172                        # inside the measure
 173                        insertionPoint.insert(0, textExp)
 174                    else:
 175                        # insertionPoint is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 176                        insertionPoint.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint.offset, textExp)
 177                else:
 178                    # extra1 is not a spanner, put the textExp right next to it
 179                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp)
 180                continue
 181
 182            if op[0] == "extrasub":
 183                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 184                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 185                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 186                # describing the change.
 187                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 188                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 189                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 190                    assert extra1 is not None
 191                    assert extra2 is not None
 192                if extra1.classes[0] != extra2.classes[0]:
 193                    textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 194                        f"changed to {extra2.classes[0]}"
 195                    )
 196                    textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 197                        f"changed from {extra1.classes[0]}"
 198                    )
 199                else:
 200                    textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]}")
 201                    textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]}")
 202                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 203                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 204                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 205                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 206                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 207                    if isinstance(insertionPoint1, m21.stream.Measure):
 208                        # insertionPoint1 is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 209                        # inside the measure
 210                        insertionPoint1.insert(0, textExp)
 211                    else:
 212                        # insertionPoint1 is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 213                        insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp)
 214                    if isinstance(insertionPoint2, m21.stream.Measure):
 215                        # insertionPoint2 is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 216                        # inside the measure
 217                        insertionPoint2.insert(0, textExp)
 218                    else:
 219                        # insertionPoint2 is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 220                        insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp)
 221                else:
 222                    # extra is not a spanner, put the textExp right next to it
 223                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)
 224                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp2)
 225                continue
 226
 227            if op[0] == "extracontentedit":
 228                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 229                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 230                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 231                # describing the change.
 232                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 233                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 234                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 235                    assert extra1 is not None
 236                    assert extra2 is not None
 237                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} text")
 238                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} text")
 239                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 240                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 241                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 242                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 243                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 244                    insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp1)
 245                    insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp2)
 246                else:
 247                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)
 248                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp2)
 249                continue
 250
 251            if op[0] == "extraoffsetedit":
 252                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 253                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 254                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 255                # describing the change.
 256                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 257                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 258                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 259                    assert extra1 is not None
 260                    assert extra2 is not None
 261                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 262                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} offset")
 263                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 264                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} offset")
 265                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 266                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 267                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 268                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 269                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 270                    insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp1)
 271                    insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp2)
 272                else:
 273                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)
 274                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp2)
 275                continue
 276
 277            if op[0] == "extradurationedit":
 278                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 279                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 280                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 281                # describing the change.
 282                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 283                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 284                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 285                    assert extra1 is not None
 286                    assert extra2 is not None
 287                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 288                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} duration")
 289                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 290                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} duration")
 291                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 292                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 293                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 294                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 295                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 296                    insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp1)
 297                    insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp2)
 298                else:
 299                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)
 300                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp2)
 301                continue
 302
 303            if op[0] == "extrastyleedit":
 304                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 305                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 306                sd1 = op[1].styledict
 307                sd2 = op[2].styledict
 308                changedStr = ""
 309                for k1, v1 in sd1.items():
 310                    if k1 not in sd2 or sd2[k1] != v1:
 311                        if changedStr:
 312                            changedStr += ","
 313                        changedStr += k1
 314
 315                # one last thing: check for keys in sd2 that aren't in sd1
 316                for k2 in sd2:
 317                    if k2 not in sd1:
 318                        if changedStr:
 319                            changedStr += ","
 320                        changedStr += k2
 321
 322                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR,
 323                # and add a textExpression describing the change.
 324                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 325                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 326                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 327                    assert extra1 is not None
 328                    assert extra2 is not None
 329
 330                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 331                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} {changedStr}")
 332                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 333                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} {changedStr}")
 334                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 335                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 336                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 337                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 338                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 339                    insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp1)
 340                    insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp2)
 341                else:
 342                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)
 343                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp2)
 344                continue
 345
 346            # staff groups
 347            if op[0] == "staffgrpins":
 348                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
 349                # add a textExpression describing the insertion.
 350                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
 351                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
 352                )
 353                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 354                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
 355                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted StaffGroup")
 356                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 357                # insert text at offset 0 in first measure of first part in group
 358                insertionSite = staffGroup2.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 359                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp)
 360                continue
 361
 362            if op[0] == "staffgrpdel":
 363                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
 364                # add a textExpression describing the deletion.
 365                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
 366                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
 367                )
 368                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 369                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
 370                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted StaffGroup")
 371                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 372                # insert text at offset 0 in first measure of first part in group
 373                insertionSite = staffGroup1.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 374                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp)
 375                continue
 376
 377            if op[0] == "staffgrpsub":
 378                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
 379                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
 380                # add a textExpression describing the change.
 381                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
 382                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
 383                )
 384                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
 385                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
 386                )
 387                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 388                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
 389                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
 390                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup")
 391                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup")
 392                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 393                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 394                # insert text at offset 0 in first measure of first part in group
 395                insertionSite = staffGroup1.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 396                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp1)
 397                insertionSite = staffGroup2.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 398                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp2)
 399                continue
 400
 401            if op[0] == "staffgrpnameedit":
 402                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
 403                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
 404                # add a textExpression describing the change.
 405                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
 406                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
 407                )
 408                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
 409                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
 410                )
 411                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 412                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
 413                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
 414                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup name")
 415                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup name")
 416                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 417                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 418                # insert text at offset 0 in first measure of first part in group
 419                insertionSite = staffGroup1.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 420                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp1)
 421                insertionSite = staffGroup2.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 422                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp2)
 423                continue
 424
 425            if op[0] == "staffgrpabbreviationedit":
 426                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
 427                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
 428                # add a textExpression describing the change.
 429                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
 430                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
 431                )
 432                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
 433                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
 434                )
 435                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 436                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
 437                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
 438                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup abbreviation")
 439                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup abbreviation")
 440                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 441                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 442                # insert text at offset 0 in first measure of first part in group
 443                insertionSite = staffGroup1.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 444                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp1)
 445                insertionSite = staffGroup2.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 446                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp2)
 447                continue
 448
 449            if op[0] == "staffgrpsymboledit":
 450                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
 451                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
 452                # add a textExpression describing the change.
 453                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
 454                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
 455                )
 456                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
 457                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
 458                )
 459                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 460                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
 461                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
 462                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup symbol shape")
 463                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup symbol shape")
 464                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 465                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 466                # insert text at offset 0 in first measure of first part in group
 467                insertionSite = staffGroup1.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 468                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp1)
 469                insertionSite = staffGroup2.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 470                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp2)
 471                continue
 472
 473            if op[0] == "staffgrpbartogetheredit":
 474                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
 475                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
 476                # add a textExpression describing the change.
 477                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
 478                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
 479                )
 480                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
 481                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
 482                )
 483                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 484                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
 485                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
 486                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup barline type")
 487                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup barline type")
 488                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 489                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 490                # insert text at offset 0 in first measure of first part in group
 491                insertionSite = staffGroup1.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 492                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp1)
 493                insertionSite = staffGroup2.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 494                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp2)
 495                continue
 496
 497            if op[0] == "staffgrppartindicesedit":
 498                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
 499                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
 500                # add a textExpression describing the change.
 501                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
 502                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
 503                )
 504                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
 505                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
 506                )
 507                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 508                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
 509                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
 510                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup parts")
 511                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup parts")
 512                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 513                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 514                # insert text at offset 0 in first measure of first part in group
 515                insertionSite = staffGroup1.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 516                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp1)
 517                insertionSite = staffGroup2.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 518                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp2)
 519                continue
 520
 521            # note
 522            if op[0] == "noteins":
 523                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnNote)
 524                # color the inserted score2 general note (note, chord, or rest)
 525                # using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 526                # The note that was inserted may in fact be a note within a chord,
 527                # so be careful to use the chord and the note in that case for
 528                # the appropriate operations.
 529                noteOrChord2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].general_note)  # type: ignore
 530                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 531                    assert noteOrChord2 is not None
 532                if len(op) >= 5 and op[4] is not None:
 533                    note2 = noteOrChord2.notes[op[4]]
 534                else:
 535                    note2 = noteOrChord2
 536                note2.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 537                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 538                    f"inserted {note2.classes[0]}")
 539                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 540                noteOrChord2.activeSite.insert(noteOrChord2.offset, textExp)
 541                continue
 542
 543            if op[0] == "notedel":
 544                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnNote)
 545                # color the deleted score1 general note (note, chord, or rest)
 546                # using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 547                # The note that was deleted may in fact be a note within a chord,
 548                # so be careful to use the chord and the note in that case for
 549                # the appropriate operations.
 550                noteOrChord1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].general_note)  # type: ignore
 551                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 552                    assert noteOrChord1 is not None
 553                if len(op) >= 5 and op[4] is not None:
 554                    note1 = noteOrChord1.notes[op[4]]
 555                else:
 556                    note1 = noteOrChord1
 557                note1.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 558                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"deleted {note1.classes[0]}")
 559                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 560                noteOrChord1.activeSite.insert(noteOrChord1.offset, textExp)
 561                continue

 966                        if changedStr:
 967                            changedStr += ","
 968                        changedStr += k1

 971                for k2 in sd2:
 972                    if k2 not in sd1:
 973                        if changedStr:
 974                            changedStr += ","
 975                        changedStr += k2

1557                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1558                    assert note2 is not None
1559                note2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1560                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric offset")
1561                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1562                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1563                continue
1564
1565            if op[0] == "lyricstyleedit":
1566                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
1567                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
1568                # color the modified note (in both scores) using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1569                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1570                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1571                    assert note1 is not None
1572                note1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1573                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric style")
1574                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1575                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1576
1577                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1578                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1579                    assert note2 is not None
1580                note2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1581                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric style")
1582                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1583                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1584                continue
1585
1586            print(
1587                f"Annotation type {op[0]} not yet supported for visualization",
1588                file=sys.stderr
1589            )
1590
1591    @staticmethod
1592    def show_diffs(
1593        score1: m21.stream.Score,
1594        score2: m21.stream.Score,
1595        out_path1: str | Path | None = None,
1596        out_path2: str | Path | None = None
1597    ) -> None:
1598        """
1599        Render two (presumably marked-up) music21 scores.  If both out_path1 and
1600        out_path2 are not None, save the rendered PDFs at those two locations,
1601        otherwise just display them using the default PDF viewer on the system.
1602
1603        Args:
1604            score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score to render
1605            score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score to render
1606            out_path1 (str, Path): Where to save the first marked-up rendered score PDF.
1607                If out_path1 is None, both PDFs will be displayed in the default PDF viewer.
1608                (default is None)
1609            out_path2 (str, Path): Where to save the second marked-up rendered score PDF.
1610                If out_path2 is None, both PDFs will be displayed in the default PDF viewer.
1611                (default is None)
1612        """
1613        # display the two (presumably annotated) scores
1614        originalComposer1: str | None = None
1615        originalComposer2: str | None = None
1616
1617        if score1.metadata is None:
1618            score1.metadata = m21.metadata.Metadata()
1619        if score2.metadata is None:
1620            score2.metadata = m21.metadata.Metadata()
1621
1622        originalComposer1 = score1.metadata.composer
1623        if originalComposer1 is None:
1624            score1.metadata.composer = "score1"
1625        else:
1626            score1.metadata.composer = "score1          " + originalComposer1
1627
1628        originalComposer2 = score2.metadata.composer
1629        if originalComposer2 is None:
1630            score2.metadata.composer = "score2"
1631        else:
1632            score2.metadata.composer = "score2          " + originalComposer2
1633
1634        # save files if requested
1635        if (out_path1 is not None) and (out_path2 is not None):
1636            score1.write("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False, fp=out_path1)
1637            score2.write("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False, fp=out_path2)
1638            print(f"Annotated scores saved in {out_path1} and {out_path2}.", file=sys.stderr)
1639        else:
1640            # just display the scores
1641            score1.show("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False)
1642            score2.show("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False)
1643
1644    @staticmethod
1645    def _location_of(m21obj: m21.base.Music21Object, score: m21.stream.Score) -> str:
1646        output: str
1647        meas: m21.stream.Stream | None
1648        part: m21.stream.Stream | None
1649        staffNum: int
1650        fractionalBeats: OffsetQL
1651
1652        if isinstance(m21obj, (m21.metadata.Metadata, m21.layout.StaffGroup)):
1653            # These are not in the timeline.  Put them first (there may be a
1654            # a measure 0/staff 0, but the first beat of that measure is beat 1).
1655            output = "measure 0, staff 0, beat 0.0"
1656            return output
1657
1658        if isinstance(m21obj, m21.spanner.RepeatBracket):
1659            # spans measures, location is start of first measure in RepeatBracket
1660            meas = m21obj.getFirst()
1661            if not isinstance(meas, m21.stream.Measure):
1662                return ""
1663            part = score.containerInHierarchy(meas)
1664            if not isinstance(part, m21.stream.Part):
1665                return ""
1666            staffNum = M21Utils.get_part_index(part, score)
1667            staffNum += 1  # staff number is 1-based
1668            output = f"measure {M21Utils.get_measure_number_with_suffix(meas, part)}, "
1669            output += f"staff {staffNum}, "
1670            fractionalBeats = 1.
1671            output += f"beat {M21Utils.ql_to_string(fractionalBeats)}"
1672            return output
1673
1674        # measure
1675        if isinstance(m21obj, m21.stream.Measure):
1676            part = score.containerInHierarchy(m21obj)
1677            if not isinstance(part, m21.stream.Part):
1678                return ""
1679            staffNum = M21Utils.get_part_index(part, score)
1680            staffNum += 1  # staffNum is 1-based
1681            output = f"measure {M21Utils.get_measure_number_with_suffix(m21obj, part)}, "
1682            output += f"staff {staffNum}, "
1683            fractionalBeats = 1.
1684            output += f"beat {M21Utils.ql_to_string(fractionalBeats)}"
1685            return output
1686
1687        # voice
1688        if isinstance(m21obj, m21.stream.Voice):
1689            meas = score.containerInHierarchy(m21obj)
1690            if not isinstance(meas, m21.stream.Measure):
1691                return ""
1692            part = score.containerInHierarchy(meas)
1693            if not isinstance(part, m21.stream.Part):
1694                return ""
1695            staffNum = M21Utils.get_part_index(part, score)
1696            staffNum += 1  # staffNum is 1-based
1697            voiceStartOffset: OffsetQL = m21obj.getOffsetInHierarchy(meas)
1698            output = f"measure {M21Utils.get_measure_number_with_suffix(meas, part)}, "
1699            output += f"staff {staffNum}, "
1700            ts: m21.meter.TimeSignature | None = m21obj.getContextByClass(m21.meter.TimeSignature)
1701            if ts is None:
1702                ts = m21.meter.TimeSignature()  # 4/4
1703            fractionalBeats = M21Utils.get_beats(voiceStartOffset, ts)
1704            output += f"beat {M21Utils.ql_to_string(fractionalBeats)}"
1705            return output
1706
1707        # spanner
1708        if isinstance(m21obj, m21.spanner.Spanner):
1709            first: m21.base.Music21Object | None = m21obj.getFirst()
1710            if first is None:
1711                return ""
1712            m21obj = first
1713            # fall through to handle normal non-stream/non-spanner m21obj
1714
1715        # normal object (not stream, not spanner)
1716        container: m21.stream.Stream | None = score.containerInHierarchy(m21obj)
1717        if isinstance(container, m21.stream.Measure):
1718            meas = container
1719        elif isinstance(container, m21.stream.Voice):
1720            meas = score.containerInHierarchy(container)
1721            if not isinstance(meas, m21.stream.Measure):
1722                return ""
1723        else:
1724            return ""
1725
1726        part = score.containerInHierarchy(meas)
1727        if not isinstance(part, m21.stream.Part):
1728            return ""
1729        staffNum = M21Utils.get_part_index(part, score)
1730        staffNum += 1  # staffNum is 1-based
1731        startOffset: OffsetQL = m21obj.getOffsetInHierarchy(meas)
1732        output = f"measure {M21Utils.get_measure_number_with_suffix(meas, part)}, "
1733        output += f"staff {staffNum}, "
1734        ts = m21obj.getContextByClass(m21.meter.TimeSignature)
1735        if ts is None:
1736            ts = m21.meter.TimeSignature()  # 4/4
1737        fractionalBeats = M21Utils.get_beats(startOffset, ts)
1738        output += f"beat {M21Utils.ql_to_string(fractionalBeats)}"
1739        return output
1740
1741    @staticmethod
1742    def get_text_output(
1743        score1: m21.stream.Score,
1744        score2: m21.stream.Score,
1745        operations: list[tuple],
1746        score1Name: str | Path | None = None,
1747        score2Name: str | Path | None = None
1748    ) -> str:
1749        """
1750        Generate text output from the differences described by an operations list
1751        (e.g. a list returned from `musicdiff.Comparison.annotated_scores_diff`).
1752
1753        Args:
1754            score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score that was compared
1755            score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score that was compared
1756            operations (list[tuple]): The operations list that describes the difference
1757                between the two scores
1758            score1Name (str | Path | None): The name to use for the first score in the text output
1759            score2Name (str | Path | None): The name to use for the second score in the text output
1760        """
1761        output: str
1762        outputList: list[str] = []
1763        oneOutput: str  # one string, multiple lines (with \n at end of all but last line)
1764
1765        for op in operations:
1766            # bar
1767            if op[0] == "insbar":
1768                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMeasure)
1769                measure2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].measure)  # type: ignore
1770                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1771                    assert measure2 is not None
1772                newLine: str = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(measure2, score2)} @@\n"
1773                oneOutput = newLine
1774                newLine = f"+(measure) {op[2].readable_str()}"
1775                oneOutput += newLine
1776                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1777                continue
1778
1779            if op[0] == "delbar":
1780                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMeasure)
1781                measure1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].measure)  # type: ignore
1782                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1783                    assert measure1 is not None
1784                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(measure1, score1)} @@\n"
1785                oneOutput = newLine
1786                newLine = f"-(measure) {op[1].readable_str()}"
1787                oneOutput += newLine
1788                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1789                continue
1790
1791            # voices
1792            if op[0] == "voiceins":
1793                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnVoice)
1794                voice2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].voice)  # type: ignore
1795                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1796                    assert voice2 is not None
1797                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(voice2, score2)} @@\n"
1798                oneOutput = newLine
1799                newLine = f"+(voice) {op[2].readable_str()}"
1800                oneOutput += newLine
1801                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1802                continue
1803
1804            if op[0] == "voicedel":
1805                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnVoice)
1806                voice1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].voice)  # type: ignore
1807                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1808                    assert voice1 is not None
1809                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(voice1, score1)} @@\n"
1810                oneOutput = newLine
1811                newLine = f"-(voice) {op[1].readable_str()}"
1812                oneOutput += newLine
1813                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1814                continue
1815
1816            # extra
1817            if op[0] == "extrains":
1818                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1819                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1820                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1821                    assert extra2 is not None
1822                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra2, score2)} @@\n"
1823                oneOutput = newLine
1824                newLine = f"+({extra2.classes[0]}) {op[2].readable_str()}"
1825                oneOutput += newLine
1826                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1827                continue
1828
1829            if op[0] == "extradel":
1830                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1831                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
1832                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1833                    assert extra1 is not None
1834                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra1, score1)} @@\n"
1835                oneOutput = newLine
1836                newLine = f"-({extra1.classes[0]}) {op[1].readable_str()}"
1837                oneOutput += newLine
1838                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1839                continue
1840
1841            if op[0] == "extrasub":
1842                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1843                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1844                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
1845                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1846                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1847                    assert extra1 is not None
1848                    assert extra2 is not None
1849                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra1, score1)} @@\n"
1850                oneOutput = newLine
1851                newLine = f"-({extra1.classes[0]}) {op[1].readable_str()}"
1852                oneOutput += newLine
1853                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
1854                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
1855                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra2, score2)} @@\n"
1856                    oneOutput = newLine
1857                else:
1858                    oneOutput += "\n"
1859                newLine = f"+({extra2.classes[0]}) {op[2].readable_str()}"
1860                oneOutput += newLine
1861                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1862                continue
1863
1864            if op[0] == "extracontentedit":
1865                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1866                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1867                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
1868                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1869                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1870                    assert extra1 is not None
1871                    assert extra2 is not None
1872                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra1, score1)} @@\n"
1873                oneOutput = newLine
1874                newLine = f"-({extra1.classes[0]}:content) {op[1].readable_str('content')}"
1875                oneOutput += newLine
1876                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
1877                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
1878                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra2, score2)} @@\n"
1879                    oneOutput = newLine
1880                else:
1881                    oneOutput += "\n"
1882                newLine = f"+({extra2.classes[0]}:content) {op[2].readable_str('content')}"
1883                oneOutput += newLine
1884                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1885                continue
1886
1887            if op[0] == "extraoffsetedit":
1888                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1889                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1890                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
1891                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1892                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1893                    assert extra1 is not None
1894                    assert extra2 is not None
1895                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra1, score1)} @@\n"
1896                oneOutput = newLine
1897                newLine = f"-({extra1.classes[0]}:offset) {op[1].readable_str('offset')}"
1898                oneOutput += newLine
1899                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1900
1901                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra2, score2)} @@\n"
1902                oneOutput = newLine
1903                newLine = f"+({extra2.classes[0]}:offset) {op[2].readable_str('offset')}"
1904                oneOutput += newLine
1905                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1906                continue
1907
1908            if op[0] == "extradurationedit":
1909                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1910                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1911                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
1912                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1913                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1914                    assert extra1 is not None
1915                    assert extra2 is not None
1916                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra1, score1)} @@\n"
1917                oneOutput = newLine
1918                newLine = f"-({extra1.classes[0]}:dur) {op[1].readable_str('duration')}"
1919                oneOutput += newLine
1920                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
1921                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
1922                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra2, score2)} @@\n"
1923                    oneOutput = newLine
1924                else:
1925                    oneOutput += "\n"
1926                newLine = f"+({extra2.classes[0]}:dur) {op[2].readable_str('duration')}"
1927                oneOutput += newLine
1928                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1929                continue
1930
1931            if op[0] == "extrastyleedit":
1932                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1933                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1934                sd1 = op[1].styledict
1935                sd2 = op[2].styledict
1936                changedStr = ""
1937                for k1, v1 in sd1.items():
1938                    if k1 not in sd2 or sd2[k1] != v1:
1939                        if changedStr:
1940                            changedStr += ","
1941                        changedStr += k1
1942
1943                # one last thing: check for keys in sd2 that aren't in sd1
1944                for k2 in sd2:
1945                    if k2 not in sd1:
1946                        if changedStr:
1947                            changedStr += ","
1948                        changedStr += k2
1949
1950                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
1951                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1952                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1953                    assert extra1 is not None
1954                    assert extra2 is not None
1955                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra1, score1)} @@\n"
1956                oneOutput = newLine
1957                style1: str = op[1].readable_str('style', changedStr=changedStr)
1958                style2: str = op[2].readable_str('style', changedStr=changedStr)
1959                newLine = f"-({extra1.classes[0]}:{changedStr}) {style1}"
1960                oneOutput += newLine
1961                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
1962                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
1963                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra2, score2)} @@\n"
1964                    oneOutput = newLine
1965                else:
1966                    oneOutput += "\n"
1967                newLine = f"+({extra2.classes[0]}:{changedStr}) {style2}"
1968                oneOutput += newLine
1969                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1970                continue
1971
1972            # staff groups
1973            if op[0] == "staffgrpins":
1974                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
1975                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
1976                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
1977                )
1978                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1979                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
1980                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(staffGroup2, score2)} @@\n"
1981                oneOutput = newLine
1982                newLine = f"+(StaffGroup) {op[2].readable_str()}"
1983                oneOutput += newLine
1984                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1985                continue
1986
1987            if op[0] == "staffgrpdel":
1988                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
1989                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
1990                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
1991                )
1992                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1993                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
1994                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(staffGroup1, score1)} @@\n"
1995                oneOutput = newLine
1996                newLine = f"-(StaffGroup) {op[1].readable_str()}"
1997                oneOutput += newLine
1998                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1999                continue
2000
2001            if op[0] == "staffgrpsub":
2002                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
2003                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
2004                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
2005                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
2006                )
2007                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
2008                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
2009                )
2010                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2011                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
2012                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
2013                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(staffGroup1, score1)} @@\n"
2014                oneOutput = newLine
2015                newLine = f"-(StaffGroup) {op[1].readable_str()}\n"
2016                oneOutput += newLine
2017                newLine = f"+(StaffGroup) {op[2].readable_str()}"
2018                oneOutput += newLine
2019                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2020                continue
2021
2022            if op[0] == "staffgrpnameedit":
2023                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
2024                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
2025                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
2026                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
2027                )
2028                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
2029                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
2030                )
2031                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2032                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
2033                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
2034                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(staffGroup1, score1)} @@\n"
2035                oneOutput = newLine
2036                newLine = f"-(StaffGroup:name) {op[1].readable_str('name')}\n"
2037                oneOutput += newLine
2038                newLine = f"+(StaffGroup:name) {op[2].readable_str('name')}"
2039                oneOutput += newLine
2040                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2041                continue
2042
2043            if op[0] == "staffgrpabbreviationedit":
2044                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
2045                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
2046                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
2047                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
2048                )
2049                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
2050                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
2051                )
2052                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2053                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
2054                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
2055                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(staffGroup1, score1)} @@\n"
2056                oneOutput = newLine
2057                newLine = f"-(StaffGroup:abbr) {op[1].readable_str('abbr')}\n"
2058                oneOutput += newLine
2059                newLine = f"+(StaffGroup:abbr) {op[2].readable_str('abbr')}"
2060                oneOutput += newLine
2061                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2062                continue
2063
2064            if op[0] == "staffgrpsymboledit":
2065                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
2066                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
2067                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
2068                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
2069                )
2070                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
2071                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
2072                )
2073                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2074                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
2075                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
2076                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(staffGroup1, score1)} @@\n"
2077                oneOutput = newLine
2078                newLine = f"-(StaffGroup:sym) {op[1].readable_str('sym')}\n"
2079                oneOutput += newLine
2080                newLine = f"+(StaffGroup:sym) {op[2].readable_str('sym')}"
2081                oneOutput += newLine
2082                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2083                continue
2084
2085            if op[0] == "staffgrpbartogetheredit":
2086                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnStaffGroup)
2087                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
2088                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
2089                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
2090                )
2091                staffGroup2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(
2092                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
2093                )
2094                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2095                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
2096                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
2097                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(staffGroup1, score1)} @@\n"
2098                oneOutput = newLine
