2600                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note2, score2)} @@\n"
2601                oneOutput = newLine
2602                newLine = f"+(Lyric) {op[2].readable_str('')}"
2603                oneOutput += newLine
2604                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2605                continue
2606
2607            if op[0] == "lyricdel":
2608                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
2609                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2610                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2611                    assert note1 is not None
2612                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note1, score1)} @@\n"
2613                oneOutput = newLine
2614                newLine = f"-(Lyric) {op[1].readable_str('')}"
2615                oneOutput += newLine
2616                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2617                continue
2618
2619            if op[0] == "lyricsub":
2620                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
2621                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
2622                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2623                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2624                    assert note1 is not None
2625                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2626                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2627                    assert note2 is not None
2628                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note1, score1)} @@\n"
2629                oneOutput = newLine
2630                newLine = f"-(Lyric) {op[1].readable_str('')}"
2631                oneOutput += newLine
2632                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
2633                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
2634                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note2, score2)} @@\n"
2635                    oneOutput = newLine
2636                else:
2637                    oneOutput += "\n"
2638                newLine = f"+(Lyric) {op[2].readable_str('')}"
2639                oneOutput += newLine
2640                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2641                continue
2642
2643            if op[0] == "lyricedit":
2644                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
2645                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
2646                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2647                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2648                    assert note1 is not None
2649                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2650                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2651                    assert note2 is not None
2652                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note1, score1)} @@\n"
2653                oneOutput = newLine
2654                newLine = f"-(Lyric:rawtext) {op[1].readable_str('rawtext')}"
2655                oneOutput += newLine
2656                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
2657                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
2658                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note2, score2)} @@\n"
2659                    oneOutput = newLine
2660                else:
2661                    oneOutput += "\n"
2662                newLine = f"+(Lyric:rawtext) {op[2].readable_str('rawtext')}"
2663                oneOutput += newLine
2664                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2665                continue
2666
2667            if op[0] == "lyricnumedit":
2668                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
2669                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
2670                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2671                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2672                    assert note1 is not None
2673                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2674                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2675                    assert note2 is not None
2676                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note1, score1)} @@\n"
2677                oneOutput = newLine
2678                newLine = f"-(Lyric:number) {op[1].readable_str('number')}"
2679                oneOutput += newLine
2680                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
2681                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
2682                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note2, score2)} @@\n"
2683                    oneOutput = newLine
2684                else:
2685                    oneOutput += "\n"
2686                newLine = f"+(Lyric:number) {op[2].readable_str('number')}"
2687                oneOutput += newLine
2688                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2689                continue
2690
2691            if op[0] == "lyricidedit":
2692                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
2693                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
2694                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2695                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2696                    assert note1 is not None
2697                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2698                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2699                    assert note2 is not None
2700                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note1, score1)} @@\n"
2701                oneOutput = newLine
2702                newLine = f"-(Lyric:id) {op[1].readable_str('id')}"
2703                oneOutput += newLine
2704                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
2705                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
2706                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note2, score2)} @@\n"
2707                    oneOutput = newLine
2708                else:
2709                    oneOutput += "\n"
2710                newLine = f"+(Lyric:id) {op[2].readable_str('id')}"
2711                oneOutput += newLine
2712                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2713                continue
2714
2715            if op[0] == "lyricoffsetedit":
2716                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
2717                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
2718                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2719                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2720                    assert note1 is not None
2721                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2722                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2723                    assert note2 is not None
2724                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note1, score1)} @@\n"
2725                oneOutput = newLine
2726                newLine = f"-(Lyric:offset) {op[1].readable_str('offset')}\n"
2727                oneOutput += newLine
2728                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note2, score2)} @@\n"
2729                oneOutput += newLine
2730                newLine = f"+(Lyric:offset) {op[2].readable_str('offset')}"
2731                oneOutput += newLine
2732                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2733                continue
2734
2735            if op[0] == "lyricstyleedit":
2736                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
2737                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
2738                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2739                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2740                    assert note1 is not None
2741                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2742                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2743                    assert note2 is not None
2744                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note1, score1)} @@\n"
2745                oneOutput = newLine
2746                newLine = f"-(Lyric:style) {op[1].readable_str('style')}"
2747                oneOutput += newLine
2748                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
2749                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
2750                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note2, score2)} @@\n"
2751                    oneOutput = newLine
2752                else:
2753                    oneOutput += "\n"
2754                newLine = f"+(Lyric:style) {op[2].readable_str('style')}"
2755                oneOutput += newLine
2756                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2757                continue
2758
2759            # metadata
2760            if op[0] == "mditemins":
2761                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMetadataItem)
2762                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(score1.metadata, score1)} @@\n"
2763                oneOutput = newLine
2764                newLine = f"+(metadata) {op[1].readable_str()}"
2765                oneOutput += newLine
2766                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2767                continue
2768
2769            if op[0] == "mditemdel":
2770                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMetadataItem)
2771                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(score1.metadata, score1)} @@\n"
2772                oneOutput = newLine
2773                newLine = f"-(metadata) {op[1].readable_str()}"
2774                oneOutput += newLine
2775                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2776                continue
2777
2778            if op[0] == "mditemsub":
2779                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMetadataItem)
2780                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMetadataItem)
2781                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(score1.metadata, score1)} @@\n"
2782                oneOutput = newLine
2783                newLine = f"-(metadata) {op[1].readable_str()}\n"
2784                oneOutput += newLine
2785                newLine = f"+(metadata) {op[2].readable_str()}"
2786                oneOutput += newLine
2787                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2788                continue
2789
2790            if op[0] == "mditemkeyedit":
2791                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMetadataItem)
2792                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMetadataItem)
2793                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(score1.metadata, score1)} @@\n"
2794                oneOutput = newLine
2795                newLine = f"-(metadata:key) {op[1].readable_str()}\n"
2796                oneOutput += newLine
2797                newLine = f"+(metadata:key) {op[2].readable_str()}"
2798                oneOutput += newLine
2799                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2800                continue
2801
2802            if op[0] == "mditemvalueedit":
2803                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMetadataItem)
2804                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMetadataItem)
2805                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(score1.metadata, score1)} @@\n"
2806                oneOutput = newLine
2807                newLine = f"-(metadata:value) {op[1].readable_str()}\n"
2808                oneOutput += newLine
2809                newLine = f"+(metadata:value) {op[2].readable_str()}"
2810                oneOutput += newLine
2811                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2812                continue
2813
2814            print(
2815                f"Annotation type {op[0]} not yet supported for visualization",
2816                file=sys.stderr
2817            )
2818
2819        # Sort by measure number (int), then measure number suffix (str), then part
2820        # number, and then beat (as parsed from "@@ measure 3b, staff 2, beat 1.5 @@")
2821        # The goal is for all measure 0's to be printed first (with measure 0's staff 0
2822        # first), with the contents of each staff of each measure coming out in beat order.
2823        LOC_PATTERN: str = (
2824            r"\@\@ measure (\d+)(\w*), staff (\d+), beat (\d+|\d+[./]\d+|\d+ \d+/\d+) \@\@"
2825        )
2826        def measNum(s: str) -> int:
2827            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2828            if not m:
2829                return -1
2830            measNumStr: str = m.group(1)
2831            measNum: int = -1
2832            try:
2833                measNum = int(measNumStr)
2834            except Exception:
2835                pass
2836            return measNum
2837
2838        def measSuf(s: str) -> str:
2839            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2840            if not m:
2841                return ''
2842            measSuf: str = m.group(2)
2843            return measSuf
2844
2845        def staffNum(s: str) -> int:
2846            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2847            if not m:
2848                return -1
2849            staffNumStr: str = m.group(3)
2850            staffNum: int = -1
2851            try:
2852                staffNum = int(staffNumStr)
2853            except Exception:
2854                pass
2855            return staffNum
2856
2857        def beat(s: str) -> OffsetQL:
2858            # can be of the form "j n/m" (mixed), "n/m" (Fraction), or "n.m" (float)
2859            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2860            if not m:
2861                return 0.
2862            beatStr: str = m.group(4)
2863            beats: OffsetQL = 0.
2864            beatsFrac: Fraction = Fraction(0, 1)
2865            beatsFloat: float = 0.
2866            try:
2867                if " " in beatStr and "/" in beatStr:
2868                    # mixed fraction "j n/m"
2869                    nums: list[str] = beatStr.split(' ')
2870                    wholeNum: int = int(nums[0])
2871                    frac: Fraction = Fraction(nums[1])
2872                    beats = opFrac(wholeNum + frac)
2873                elif "/" in beatStr:
2874                    # fraction
2875                    beatsFrac = Fraction(beatStr)
2876                    beats = opFrac(beatsFrac)
2877                else:
2878                    beatsFloat = float(beatStr)
2879                    beats = opFrac(beatsFloat)
2880            except Exception:
2881                pass
2882            return beats
2883
2884        outputList.sort(key=lambda s: (measNum(s), measSuf(s), staffNum(s), beat(s)))
2885
2886        if operations:
2887            # filenames only show up at the start of text output if there are any diffs
2888            if score1Name:
2889                outputList.insert(0, f"--- {score1Name}")
2890                outputList.insert(1, f"+++ {score2Name}")
2891            else:
2892                outputList.insert(0, "--- score1")
2893                outputList.insert(1, "+++ score2")
2894
2895        output = '\n'.join(outputList)
2896        return output
class Visualization: 
  31class Visualization:
  32    # These can be set by the client to different colors
  33    INSERTED_COLOR = "red"
  34    """
  35    `INSERTED_COLOR` can be set to customize the rendered score markup that `mark_diffs` does.
  36    """
  37    DELETED_COLOR = "red"
  38    """
  39    `DELETED_COLOR` can be set to customize the rendered score markup that `mark_diffs` does.
  40    """
  41    CHANGED_COLOR = "red"
  42    """
  43    `CHANGED_COLOR` can be set to customize the rendered score markup that `mark_diffs` does.
  44    """
  45
  46    @staticmethod
  47    def mark_diffs(
  48        score1: m21.stream.Score,
  49        score2: m21.stream.Score,
  50        operations: list[tuple]
  51    ) -> None:
  52        """
  53        Mark up two music21 scores with the differences described by an operations
  54        list (e.g. a list returned from `musicdiff.Comparison.annotated_scores_diff`).
  55
  56        Args:
  57            score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score to mark up
  58            score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score to mark up
  59            operations (list[tuple]): The operations list that describes the difference
  60                between the two scores
  61        """
  62        changedStr: str
  63        for op in operations:
  64            # bar
  65            if op[0] == "insbar":
  66                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMeasure)
  67                # color all the notes in the inserted score2 measure
  68                # using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  69                measure2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].measure)  # type: ignore
  70                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
  71                    assert measure2 is not None
  72                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted measure")
  73                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  74                measure2.insert(0, textExp)
  75                measure2.style.color = (
  76                    Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  77                )  # this apparently does nothing
  78                for el in measure2.recurse().notesAndRests:
  79                    el.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  80                continue
  81
  82            if op[0] == "delbar":
  83                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMeasure)
  84                # color all the notes in the deleted score1 measure
  85                # using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  86                measure1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].measure)  # type: ignore
  87                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
  88                    assert measure1 is not None
  89                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted measure")
  90                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  91                measure1.insert(0, textExp)
  92                measure1.style.color = (
  93                    Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  94                )  # this apparently does nothing
  95                for el in measure1.recurse().notesAndRests:
  96                    el.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  97                continue
  98
  99            # voices
 100            if op[0] == "voiceins":
 101                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnVoice)
 102                # color all the notes in the inserted score2 voice
 103                # using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 104                voice2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].voice)  # type: ignore
 105                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 106                    assert voice2 is not None
 107                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted voice")
 108                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 109                voice2.insert(0, textExp)
 110
 111                voice2.style.color = (
 112                    Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 113                )  # this apparently does nothing
 114                for el in voice2.recurse().notesAndRests:
 115                    el.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 116                continue
 117
 118            if op[0] == "voicedel":
 119                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnVoice)
 120                # color all the notes in the deleted score1 voice
 121                # using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 122                voice1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].voice)  # type: ignore
 123                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 124                    assert voice1 is not None
 125                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted voice")
 126                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 127                voice1.insert(0, textExp)
 128
 129                voice1.style.color = (
 130                    Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 131                )  # this apparently does nothing
 132                for el in voice1.recurse().notesAndRests:
 133                    el.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 134                continue
 135
 136            # extra
 137            if op[0] == "extrains":
 138                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 139                # color the extra using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR,
 140                # and add a textExpression describing the insertion.
 141                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 142                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 143                    assert extra2 is not None
 144                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"inserted {extra2.classes[0]}")
 145                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 146                if isinstance(extra2, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 147                    insertionPoint = extra2.getFirst()
 148                    if isinstance(insertionPoint, m21.stream.Measure):
 149                        # insertionPoint is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 150                        # inside the measure
 151                        insertionPoint.insert(0, textExp)
 152                    else:
 153                        # insertionPoint is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 154                        insertionPoint.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint.offset, textExp)
 155                else:
 156                    # extra2 is not a spanner, put the textExp right next to it
 157                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp)
 158                continue
 159
 160            if op[0] == "extradel":
 161                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 162                # color the extra using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 163                # describing the deletion.
 164                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 165                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 166                    assert extra1 is not None
 167                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"deleted {extra1.classes[0]}")
 168                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 169                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 170                    insertionPoint = extra1.getFirst()
 171                    if isinstance(insertionPoint, m21.stream.Measure):
 172                        # insertionPoint is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 173                        # inside the measure
 174                        insertionPoint.insert(0, textExp)
 175                    else:
 176                        # insertionPoint is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 177                        insertionPoint.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint.offset, textExp)
 178                else:
 179                    # extra1 is not a spanner, put the textExp right next to it
 180                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp)
 181                continue
 182
 183            if op[0] == "extrasub":
 184                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 185                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 186                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 187                # describing the change.
 188                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 189                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 190                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 191                    assert extra1 is not None
 192                    assert extra2 is not None
 193                if extra1.classes[0] != extra2.classes[0]:
 194                    textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 195                        f"changed to {extra2.classes[0]}"
 196                    )
 197                    textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 198                        f"changed from {extra1.classes[0]}"
 199                    )
 200                else:
 201                    textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]}")
 202                    textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]}")
 203                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 204                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 205                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 206                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 207                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 208                    if isinstance(insertionPoint1, m21.stream.Measure):
 209                        # insertionPoint1 is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 210                        # inside the measure
 211                        insertionPoint1.insert(0, textExp)
 212                    else:
 213                        # insertionPoint1 is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 214                        insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp)
 215                    if isinstance(insertionPoint2, m21.stream.Measure):
 216                        # insertionPoint2 is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 217                        # inside the measure
 218                        insertionPoint2.insert(0, textExp)
 219                    else:
 220                        # insertionPoint2 is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 221                        insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp)
 222                else:
 223                    # extra is not a spanner, put the textExp right next to it
 224                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)
 225                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp2)
 226                continue
 227
 228            if op[0] == "extracontentedit":
 229                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 230                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 231                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 232                # describing the change.
 233                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 234                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 235                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 236                    assert extra1 is not None
 237                    assert extra2 is not None
 238                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} text")
 239                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} text")
 240                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 241                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 242                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 243                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 244                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 245                    insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp1)
 246                    insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp2)
 247                else:
 248                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)
 249                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp2)
 250                continue
 251
 252            if op[0] == "extraoffsetedit":
 253                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 254                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 255                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 256                # describing the change.
 257                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 258                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 259                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 260                    assert extra1 is not None
 261                    assert extra2 is not None
 262                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 263                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} offset")
 264                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 265                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} offset")
 266                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 267                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 268                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 269                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 270                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 271                    insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp1)
 272                    insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp2)
 273                else:
 274                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)

 314                        changedStr += k1

 319                        if changedStr:
 320                            changedStr += ","
 321                        changedStr += k2

 962                sd1 = op[1].styledict
 963                sd2 = op[2].styledict
 964                changedStr = ""
 965                for k1, v1 in sd1.items():
 966                    if k1 not in sd2 or sd2[k1] != v1:
 967                        if changedStr:
 968                            changedStr += ","
 969                        changedStr += k1
 970
 971                # one last thing: check for keys in sd2 that aren't in sd1
 972                for k2 in sd2:
 973                    if k2 not in sd1:
 974                        if changedStr:
 975                            changedStr += ","
 976                        changedStr += k2
 977
 978                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].general_note)  # type: ignore

 980                    assert note1 is not None

 982                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed note {changedStr}")
 983                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 984                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)

1315                    idx = op[4][1]
1316                    note2 = chord2.notes[idx]
1317                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1318                    assert note2 is not None
1319                note2.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1320                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted tie")
1321                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1322                if note2.activeSite is not None:
1323                    note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1324                else:
1325                    chord2.activeSite.insert(chord2.offset, textExp)
1326                continue
1327
1328            # expressions
1329            if op[0] == "insexpression":
1330                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnNote)
1331                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnNote)
1332                # color the note in both scores using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1333                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].general_note)  # type: ignore
1334                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1335                    assert note1 is not None
1336                note1.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1337                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted expression")
1338                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1339                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1340
1341                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].general_note)  # type: ignore
1342                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1343                    assert note2 is not None
1344                note2.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1345                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted expression")
1346                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1347                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1348                continue
1349
1350            if op[0] == "delexpression":
1351                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnNote)
1352                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnNote)
1353                # color the deleted expression in score1 using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1354                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].general_note)  # type: ignore
1355                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1356                    assert note1 is not None
1357                note1.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1358                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted expression")
1359                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1360                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1361
1362                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].general_note)  # type: ignore
1363                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1364                    assert note2 is not None
1365                note2.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1366                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted expression")
1367                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1368                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1369                continue
1370
1371            if op[0] == "editexpression":
1372                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnNote)
1373                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnNote)
1374                # color the changed beam (in both scores) using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1375                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].general_note)  # type: ignore
1376                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1377                    assert note1 is not None
1378                note1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1379                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed expression")
1380                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1381                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1382
1383                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].general_note)  # type: ignore
1384                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1385                    assert note2 is not None
1386                note2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1387                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed expression")
1388                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1389                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1390                continue
1391
1392            # articulations
1393            if op[0] == "insarticulation":
1394                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnNote)
1395                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnNote)
1396                # color the modified note in both scores using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1397                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].general_note)  # type: ignore
1398                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1399                    assert note1 is not None
1400                note1.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1401                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted articulation")
1402                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1403                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1404
1405                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].general_note)  # type: ignore
1406                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1407                    assert note2 is not None
1408                note2.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1409                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted articulation")
1410                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1411                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1412                continue
1413
1414            if op[0] == "delarticulation":
1415                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnNote)
1416                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnNote)
1417                # color the modified note in both scores using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1418                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].general_note)  # type: ignore
1419                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1420                    assert note1 is not None
1421                note1.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1422                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted articulation")
1423                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1424                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1425
1426                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].general_note)  # type: ignore
1427                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1428                    assert note2 is not None
1429                note2.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1430                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted articulation")
1431                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1432                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1433                continue
1434
1435            if op[0] == "editarticulation":
1436                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnNote)
1437                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnNote)
1438                # color the modified note (in both scores) using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1439                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].general_note)  # type: ignore
1440                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1441                    assert note1 is not None
1442                note1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1443                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed articulation")
1444                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1445                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1446
1447                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].general_note)  # type: ignore
1448                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1449                    assert note2 is not None
1450                note2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1451                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed articulation")
1452                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1453                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1454                continue
1455
1456            # lyrics
1457            if op[0] == "lyricins":
1458                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
1459                # color the note with the lyric using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1460                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1461                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1462                    assert note2 is not None
1463                note2.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1464                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted lyric")
1465                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
1466                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1467                continue
1468
1469            if op[0] == "lyricdel":
1470                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
1471                # color the note with the lyric using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1472                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1473                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1474                    assert note1 is not None
1475                note1.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1476                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted lyric")
1477                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
1478                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1479                continue
1480
1481            if op[0] in ("lyricsub", "lyricedit"):
1482                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
1483                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
1484                # color the note with changed lyric (in both scores) using
1485                # Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1486                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1487                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1488                    assert note1 is not None
1489                note1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1490                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric")
1491                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1492                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1493
1494                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1495                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1496                    assert note2 is not None
1497                note2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1498                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric")
1499                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1500                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1501                continue
1502
1503            if op[0] == "lyricnumedit":
1504                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
1505                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
1506                # color the modified note (in both scores) using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1507                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1508                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1509                    assert note1 is not None
1510                note1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1511                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric verse num")
1512                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1513                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1514
1515                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1516                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1517                    assert note2 is not None
1518                note2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1519                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric verse num")
1520                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1521                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1522                continue
1523
1524            if op[0] == "lyricidedit":
1525                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
1526                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
1527                # color the modified note (in both scores) using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1528                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1529                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1530                    assert note1 is not None
1531                note1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1532                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric verse id")
1533                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1534                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1535
1536                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1537                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1538                    assert note2 is not None
1539                note2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1540                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric verse id")
1541                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1542                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1543                continue
1544
1545            if op[0] == "lyricoffsetedit":
1546                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
1547                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
1548                # color the modified note (in both scores) using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1549                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1550                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1551                    assert note1 is not None
1552                note1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1553                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric offset")
1554                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1555                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1556
1557                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1558                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1559                    assert note2 is not None
1560                note2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1561                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric offset")
1562                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1563                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1564                continue
1565
1566            if op[0] == "lyricstyleedit":
1567                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
1568                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
1569                # color the modified note (in both scores) using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1570                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1571                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1572                    assert note1 is not None
1573                note1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1574                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric style")
1575                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1576                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1577
1578                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1579                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1580                    assert note2 is not None
1581                note2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1582                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric style")
1583                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1584                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1585                continue
1586
1587            print(
1588                f"Annotation type {op[0]} not yet supported for visualization",
1589                file=sys.stderr
1590            )

1592    @staticmethod
1593    def show_diffs(
1594        score1: m21.stream.Score,
1595        score2: m21.stream.Score,
1596        out_path1: str | Path | None = None,
1597        out_path2: str | Path | None = None
1598    ) -> None:
1599        """
1600        Render two (presumably marked-up) music21 scores.  If both out_path1 and
1601        out_path2 are not None, save the rendered PDFs at those two locations,
1602        otherwise just display them using the default PDF viewer on the system.
1603
1604        Args:
1605            score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score to render
1606            score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score to render
1607            out_path1 (str, Path): Where to save the first marked-up rendered score PDF.
1608                If out_path1 is None, both PDFs will be displayed in the default PDF viewer.
1609                (default is None)
1610            out_path2 (str, Path): Where to save the second marked-up rendered score PDF.
1611                If out_path2 is None, both PDFs will be displayed in the default PDF viewer.
1612                (default is None)
1613        """
1614        # display the two (presumably annotated) scores
1615        originalComposer1: str | None = None
1616        originalComposer2: str | None = None
1617
1618        if score1.metadata is None:
1619            score1.metadata = m21.metadata.Metadata()
1620        if score2.metadata is None:
1621            score2.metadata = m21.metadata.Metadata()
1622
1623        originalComposer1 = score1.metadata.composer
1624        if originalComposer1 is None:
1625            score1.metadata.composer = "score1"
1626        else:
1627            score1.metadata.composer = "score1          " + originalComposer1
1628
1629        originalComposer2 = score2.metadata.composer
1630        if originalComposer2 is None:
1631            score2.metadata.composer = "score2"
1632        else:
1633            score2.metadata.composer = "score2          " + originalComposer2
1634
1635        # save files if requested
1636        if (out_path1 is not None) and (out_path2 is not None):
1637            score1.write("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False, fp=out_path1)
1638            score2.write("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False, fp=out_path2)
1639            print(f"Annotated scores saved in {out_path1} and {out_path2}.", file=sys.stderr)
1640        else:
1641            # just display the scores
1642            score1.show("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False)
1643            score2.show("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False)
1644
1645    @staticmethod
1646    def _location_of(m21obj: m21.base.Music21Object, score: m21.stream.Score) -> str:
1647        output: str
1648        meas: m21.stream.Stream | None
1649        part: m21.stream.Stream | None
1650        staffNum: int
1651        fractionalBeats: OffsetQL
1652
1653        if isinstance(m21obj, (m21.metadata.Metadata, m21.layout.StaffGroup)):
1654            # These are not in the timeline.  Put them first (there may be a
1655            # a measure 0/staff 0, but the first beat of that measure is beat 1).
1656            output = "measure 0, staff 0, beat 0.0"
1657            return output
1658
1659        if isinstance(m21obj, m21.spanner.RepeatBracket):
1660            # spans measures, location is start of first measure in RepeatBracket
1661            meas = m21obj.getFirst()
1662            if not isinstance(meas, m21.stream.Measure):
1663                return ""
1664            part = score.containerInHierarchy(meas)
1665            if not isinstance(part, m21.stream.Part):
1666                return ""
1667            staffNum = M21Utils.get_part_index(part, score)
1668            staffNum += 1  # staff number is 1-based
1669            output = f"measure {M21Utils.get_measure_number_with_suffix(meas, part)}, "
1670            output += f"staff {staffNum}, "
1671            fractionalBeats = 1.
1672            output += f"beat {M21Utils.ql_to_string(fractionalBeats)}"
1673            return output
1674
1675        # measure
1676        if isinstance(m21obj, m21.stream.Measure):
1677            part = score.containerInHierarchy(m21obj)
1678            if not isinstance(part, m21.stream.Part):
1679                return ""
1680            staffNum = M21Utils.get_part_index(part, score)
1681            staffNum += 1  # staffNum is 1-based
1682            output = f"measure {M21Utils.get_measure_number_with_suffix(m21obj, part)}, "
1683            output += f"staff {staffNum}, "
1684            fractionalBeats = 1.
1685            output += f"beat {M21Utils.ql_to_string(fractionalBeats)}"
1686            return output
1687
1688        # voice
1689        if isinstance(m21obj, m21.stream.Voice):
1690            meas = score.containerInHierarchy(m21obj)
1691            if not isinstance(meas, m21.stream.Measure):
1692                return ""
1693            part = score.containerInHierarchy(meas)
1694            if not isinstance(part, m21.stream.Part):
1695                return ""
1696            staffNum = M21Utils.get_part_index(part, score)
1697            staffNum += 1  # staffNum is 1-based
1698            voiceStartOffset: OffsetQL = m21obj.getOffsetInHierarchy(meas)
1699            output = f"measure {M21Utils.get_measure_number_with_suffix(meas, part)}, "
1700            output += f"staff {staffNum}, "
1701            ts: m21.meter.TimeSignature | None = m21obj.getContextByClass(m21.meter.TimeSignature)
1702            if ts is None:
1703                ts = m21.meter.TimeSignature()  # 4/4
1704            fractionalBeats = M21Utils.get_beats(voiceStartOffset, ts)
1705            output += f"beat {M21Utils.ql_to_string(fractionalBeats)}"
1706            return output
1707
1708        # spanner
1709        if isinstance(m21obj, m21.spanner.Spanner):
1710            first: m21.base.Music21Object | None = m21obj.getFirst()
1711            if first is None:
1712                return ""
1713            m21obj = first
1714            # fall through to handle normal non-stream/non-spanner m21obj
1715
1716        # normal object (not stream, not spanner)
1717        container: m21.stream.Stream | None = score.containerInHierarchy(m21obj)
1718        if isinstance(container, m21.stream.Measure):
1719            meas = container
1720        elif isinstance(container, m21.stream.Voice):
1721            meas = score.containerInHierarchy(container)
1722            if not isinstance(meas, m21.stream.Measure):
1723                return ""
1724        else:
1725            return ""
1726
1727        part = score.containerInHierarchy(meas)
1728        if not isinstance(part, m21.stream.Part):
1729            return ""
1730        staffNum = M21Utils.get_part_index(part, score)
1731        staffNum += 1  # staffNum is 1-based
1732        startOffset: OffsetQL = m21obj.getOffsetInHierarchy(meas)
1733        output = f"measure {M21Utils.get_measure_number_with_suffix(meas, part)}, "
1734        output += f"staff {staffNum}, "
1735        ts = m21obj.getContextByClass(m21.meter.TimeSignature)
1736        if ts is None:
1737            ts = m21.meter.TimeSignature()  # 4/4
1738        fractionalBeats = M21Utils.get_beats(startOffset, ts)
1739        output += f"beat {M21Utils.ql_to_string(fractionalBeats)}"
1740        return output
1741
1742    @staticmethod
1743    def get_text_output(
1744        score1: m21.stream.Score,
1745        score2: m21.stream.Score,
1746        operations: list[tuple],
1747        score1Name: str | Path | None = None,
1748        score2Name: str | Path | None = None
1749    ) -> str:
1750        """
1751        Generate text output from the differences described by an operations list
1752        (e.g. a list returned from `musicdiff.Comparison.annotated_scores_diff`).
1753
1754        Args:
1755            score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score that was compared
1756            score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score that was compared
1757            operations (list[tuple]): The operations list that describes the difference
1758                between the two scores
1759            score1Name (str | Path | None): The name to use for the first score in the text output
1760            score2Name (str | Path | None): The name to use for the second score in the text output
1761        """
1762        output: str
1763        outputList: list[str] = []
1764        oneOutput: str  # one string, multiple lines (with \n at end of all but last line)
1765
1766        for op in operations:
1767            # bar
1768            if op[0] == "insbar":
1769                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMeasure)
1770                measure2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].measure)  # type: ignore
1771                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1772                    assert measure2 is not None
1773                newLine: str = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(measure2, score2)} @@\n"
1774                oneOutput = newLine
1775                newLine = f"+(measure) {op[2].readable_str()}"
1776                oneOutput += newLine
1777                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1778                continue
1779
1780            if op[0] == "delbar":
1781                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMeasure)
1782                measure1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].measure)  # type: ignore
1783                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1784                    assert measure1 is not None
1785                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(measure1, score1)} @@\n"
1786                oneOutput = newLine
1787                newLine = f"-(measure) {op[1].readable_str()}"
1788                oneOutput += newLine
1789                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1790                continue
1791
1792            # voices
1793            if op[0] == "voiceins":
1794                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnVoice)
1795                voice2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].voice)  # type: ignore
1796                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1797                    assert voice2 is not None
1798                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(voice2, score2)} @@\n"
1799                oneOutput = newLine
1800                newLine = f"+(voice) {op[2].readable_str()}"
1801                oneOutput += newLine
1802                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1803                continue
1804
1805            if op[0] == "voicedel":
1806                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnVoice)
1807                voice1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].voice)  # type: ignore
1808                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1809                    assert voice1 is not None
1810                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(voice1, score1)} @@\n"
1811                oneOutput = newLine
1812                newLine = f"-(voice) {op[1].readable_str()}"
1813                oneOutput += newLine
1814                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1815                continue
1816
1817            # extra
1818            if op[0] == "extrains":
1819                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1820                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1821                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1822                    assert extra2 is not None
1823                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra2, score2)} @@\n"

1942                        changedStr += k1

1949                        changedStr += k2

2819
2820        # Sort by measure number (int), then measure number suffix (str), then part
2821        # number, and then beat (as parsed from "@@ measure 3b, staff 2, beat 1.5 @@")
2822        # The goal is for all measure 0's to be printed first (with measure 0's staff 0
2823        # first), with the contents of each staff of each measure coming out in beat order.
2824        LOC_PATTERN: str = (
2825            r"\@\@ measure (\d+)(\w*), staff (\d+), beat (\d+|\d+[./]\d+|\d+ \d+/\d+) \@\@"
2826        )
2827        def measNum(s: str) -> int:
2828            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2829            if not m:
2830                return -1
2831            measNumStr: str = m.group(1)
2832            measNum: int = -1
2833            try:
2834                measNum = int(measNumStr)
2835            except Exception:
2836                pass
2837            return measNum
2838
2839        def measSuf(s: str) -> str:
2840            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2841            if not m:
2842                return ''
2843            measSuf: str = m.group(2)
2844            return measSuf
2845
2846        def staffNum(s: str) -> int:
2847            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2848            if not m:
2849                return -1
2850            staffNumStr: str = m.group(3)
2851            staffNum: int = -1
2852            try:
2853                staffNum = int(staffNumStr)
2854            except Exception:
2855                pass
2856            return staffNum
2857
2858        def beat(s: str) -> OffsetQL:
2859            # can be of the form "j n/m" (mixed), "n/m" (Fraction), or "n.m" (float)
2860            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2861            if not m:
2862                return 0.
2863            beatStr: str = m.group(4)
2864            beats: OffsetQL = 0.
2865            beatsFrac: Fraction = Fraction(0, 1)
2866            beatsFloat: float = 0.
2867            try:
2868                if " " in beatStr and "/" in beatStr:
2869                    # mixed fraction "j n/m"
2870                    nums: list[str] = beatStr.split(' ')
2871                    wholeNum: int = int(nums[0])
2872                    frac: Fraction = Fraction(nums[1])
2873                    beats = opFrac(wholeNum + frac)
2874                elif "/" in beatStr:
2875                    # fraction
2876                    beatsFrac = Fraction(beatStr)
2877                    beats = opFrac(beatsFrac)
2878                else:
2879                    beatsFloat = float(beatStr)
2880                    beats = opFrac(beatsFloat)
2881            except Exception:
2882                pass
2883            return beats
2884
2885        outputList.sort(key=lambda s: (measNum(s), measSuf(s), staffNum(s), beat(s)))
2886
2887        if operations:
2888            # filenames only show up at the start of text output if there are any diffs
2889            if score1Name:
2890                outputList.insert(0, f"--- {score1Name}")
2891                outputList.insert(1, f"+++ {score2Name}")
2892            else:
2893                outputList.insert(0, "--- score1")
2894                outputList.insert(1, "+++ score2")
2895
2896        output = '\n'.join(outputList)
2897        return output
INSERTED_COLOR = 'red'

INSERTED_COLOR can be set to customize the rendered score markup that mark_diffs does.

DELETED_COLOR = 'red'

DELETED_COLOR can be set to customize the rendered score markup that mark_diffs does.

CHANGED_COLOR = 'red'

CHANGED_COLOR can be set to customize the rendered score markup that mark_diffs does.

@staticmethod
def mark_diffs( score1: music21.stream.base.Score, score2: music21.stream.base.Score, operations: list[tuple]) -> None: 
  46    @staticmethod
  47    def mark_diffs(
  48        score1: m21.stream.Score,
  49        score2: m21.stream.Score,
  50        operations: list[tuple]
  51    ) -> None:
  52        """
  53        Mark up two music21 scores with the differences described by an operations
  54        list (e.g. a list returned from `musicdiff.Comparison.annotated_scores_diff`).
  55
  56        Args:
  57            score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score to mark up
  58            score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score to mark up
  59            operations (list[tuple]): The operations list that describes the difference
  60                between the two scores
  61        """
  62        changedStr: str
  63        for op in operations:
  64            # bar
  65            if op[0] == "insbar":
  66                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMeasure)
  67                # color all the notes in the inserted score2 measure
  68                # using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  69                measure2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].measure)  # type: ignore
  70                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
  71                    assert measure2 is not None
  72                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted measure")
  73                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  74                measure2.insert(0, textExp)
  75                measure2.style.color = (
  76                    Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  77                )  # this apparently does nothing
  78                for el in measure2.recurse().notesAndRests:
  79                    el.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
  80                continue
  81
  82            if op[0] == "delbar":
  83                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMeasure)
  84                # color all the notes in the deleted score1 measure
  85                # using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  86                measure1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].measure)  # type: ignore
  87                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
  88                    assert measure1 is not None
  89                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted measure")
  90                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  91                measure1.insert(0, textExp)
  92                measure1.style.color = (
  93                    Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  94                )  # this apparently does nothing
  95                for el in measure1.recurse().notesAndRests:
  96                    el.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
  97                continue
  98
  99            # voices
 100            if op[0] == "voiceins":
 101                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnVoice)
 102                # color all the notes in the inserted score2 voice
 103                # using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 104                voice2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].voice)  # type: ignore
 105                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 106                    assert voice2 is not None
 107                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted voice")
 108                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 109                voice2.insert(0, textExp)
 110
 111                voice2.style.color = (
 112                    Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 113                )  # this apparently does nothing
 114                for el in voice2.recurse().notesAndRests:
 115                    el.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 116                continue
 117
 118            if op[0] == "voicedel":
 119                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnVoice)
 120                # color all the notes in the deleted score1 voice
 121                # using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 122                voice1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].voice)  # type: ignore
 123                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 124                    assert voice1 is not None
 125                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted voice")
 126                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 127                voice1.insert(0, textExp)
 128
 129                voice1.style.color = (
 130                    Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 131                )  # this apparently does nothing
 132                for el in voice1.recurse().notesAndRests:
 133                    el.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 134                continue
 135
 136            # extra
 137            if op[0] == "extrains":
 138                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 139                # color the extra using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR,
 140                # and add a textExpression describing the insertion.
 141                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 142                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 143                    assert extra2 is not None
 144                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"inserted {extra2.classes[0]}")
 145                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 146                if isinstance(extra2, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 147                    insertionPoint = extra2.getFirst()
 148                    if isinstance(insertionPoint, m21.stream.Measure):
 149                        # insertionPoint is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 150                        # inside the measure
 151                        insertionPoint.insert(0, textExp)
 152                    else:
 153                        # insertionPoint is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 154                        insertionPoint.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint.offset, textExp)
 155                else:
 156                    # extra2 is not a spanner, put the textExp right next to it
 157                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp)
 158                continue
 159
 160            if op[0] == "extradel":
 161                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 162                # color the extra using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 163                # describing the deletion.
 164                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 165                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 166                    assert extra1 is not None
 167                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"deleted {extra1.classes[0]}")
 168                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 169                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 170                    insertionPoint = extra1.getFirst()
 171                    if isinstance(insertionPoint, m21.stream.Measure):
 172                        # insertionPoint is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 173                        # inside the measure
 174                        insertionPoint.insert(0, textExp)
 175                    else:
 176                        # insertionPoint is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 177                        insertionPoint.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint.offset, textExp)
 178                else:
 179                    # extra1 is not a spanner, put the textExp right next to it
 180                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp)
 181                continue
 182
 183            if op[0] == "extrasub":
 184                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 185                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 186                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 187                # describing the change.
 188                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 189                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 190                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 191                    assert extra1 is not None
 192                    assert extra2 is not None
 193                if extra1.classes[0] != extra2.classes[0]:
 194                    textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 195                        f"changed to {extra2.classes[0]}"
 196                    )
 197                    textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 198                        f"changed from {extra1.classes[0]}"
 199                    )
 200                else:
 201                    textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]}")
 202                    textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]}")
 203                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 204                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 205                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 206                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 207                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 208                    if isinstance(insertionPoint1, m21.stream.Measure):
 209                        # insertionPoint1 is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 210                        # inside the measure
 211                        insertionPoint1.insert(0, textExp)
 212                    else:
 213                        # insertionPoint1 is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 214                        insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp)
 215                    if isinstance(insertionPoint2, m21.stream.Measure):
 216                        # insertionPoint2 is a measure, put the textExp at offset 0
 217                        # inside the measure
 218                        insertionPoint2.insert(0, textExp)
 219                    else:
 220                        # insertionPoint2 is something else, put the textExp right next to it.
 221                        insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp)
 222                else:
 223                    # extra is not a spanner, put the textExp right next to it
 224                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)
 225                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp2)
 226                continue
 227
 228            if op[0] == "extracontentedit":
 229                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 230                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 231                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 232                # describing the change.
 233                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 234                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 235                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 236                    assert extra1 is not None
 237                    assert extra2 is not None
 238                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} text")
 239                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} text")
 240                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 241                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 242                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 243                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 244                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 245                    insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp1)
 246                    insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp2)
 247                else:
 248                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)
 249                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp2)
 250                continue

 253                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 254                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 255                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 256                # describing the change.
 257                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 258                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 259                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 260                    assert extra1 is not None
 261                    assert extra2 is not None
 262                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 263                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} offset")
 264                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 265                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} offset")
 266                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 267                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 268                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 269                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 270                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 271                    insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp1)
 272                    insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp2)
 273                else:
 274                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)
 275                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp2)

 279                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
 280                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 281                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR, and add a textExpression
 282                # describing the change.
 283                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 284                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 285                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 286                    assert extra1 is not None
 287                    assert extra2 is not None
 288                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 289                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} duration")
 290                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 291                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} duration")
 292                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 293                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 294                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 295                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 296                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 297                    insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp1)
 298                    insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp2)

 306                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
 307                sd1 = op[1].styledict
 308                sd2 = op[2].styledict
 309                changedStr = ""
 310                for k1, v1 in sd1.items():
 311                    if k1 not in sd2 or sd2[k1] != v1:
 312                        if changedStr:
 313                            changedStr += ","
 314                        changedStr += k1
 315
 316                # one last thing: check for keys in sd2 that aren't in sd1
 317                for k2 in sd2:
 318                    if k2 not in sd1:
 319                        if changedStr:
 320                            changedStr += ","
 321                        changedStr += k2
 322
 323                # color the extra using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR,
 324                # and add a textExpression describing the change.
 325                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
 326                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
 327                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 328                    assert extra1 is not None
 329                    assert extra2 is not None
 330

 332                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} {changedStr}")
 333                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 334                    f"changed {extra1.classes[0]} {changedStr}")
 335                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 336                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 337                if isinstance(extra1, m21.spanner.Spanner):
 338                    insertionPoint1 = extra1.getFirst()
 339                    insertionPoint2 = extra2.getFirst()
 340                    insertionPoint1.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint1.offset, textExp1)
 341                    insertionPoint2.activeSite.insert(insertionPoint2.offset, textExp2)
 342                else:
 343                    extra1.activeSite.insert(extra1.offset, textExp1)
 344                    extra2.activeSite.insert(extra2.offset, textExp2)
 345                continue

 349                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnStaffGroup)
 350                # add a textExpression describing the insertion.

 352                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
 353                )

 355                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
 356                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("inserted StaffGroup")
 357                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR

 359                insertionSite = staffGroup2.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 360                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp)

 365                # add a textExpression describing the deletion.
 366                staffGroup1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(
 367                    op[1].staff_group  # type: ignore
 368                )
 369                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 370                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
 371                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("deleted StaffGroup")
 372                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR

 386                    op[2].staff_group  # type: ignore
 387                )

 390                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
 391                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup")

 394                textExp2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
 395                # insert text at offset 0 in first measure of first part in group
 396                insertionSite = staffGroup1.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 397                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp1)
 398                insertionSite = staffGroup2.getFirst()[m21.stream.Measure].first()
 399                insertionSite.insert(0, textExp2)
 400                continue

 402            if op[0] == "staffgrpnameedit":

 411                )
 412                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 413                    assert staffGroup1 is not None
 414                    assert staffGroup2 is not None
 415                textExp1 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup name")
 416                textExp2 = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed StaffGroup name")
 417                textExp1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR

 522            # note
 523            if op[0] == "noteins":
