 525                # color the inserted score2 general note (note, chord, or rest)
 526                # using Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 527                # The note that was inserted may in fact be a note within a chord,
 528                # so be careful to use the chord and the note in that case for
 529                # the appropriate operations.
 530                noteOrChord2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].general_note)  # type: ignore
 531                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
 532                    assert noteOrChord2 is not None
 533                if len(op) >= 5 and op[4] is not None:

 536                    note2 = noteOrChord2
 537                note2.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 538                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression(
 539                    f"inserted {note2.classes[0]}")
 540                textExp.style.color = Visualization.INSERTED_COLOR
 541                noteOrChord2.activeSite.insert(noteOrChord2.offset, textExp)
 542                continue
 543
 544            if op[0] == "notedel":
 545                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnNote)
 546                # color the deleted score1 general note (note, chord, or rest)
 547                # using Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 548                # The note that was deleted may in fact be a note within a chord,
 549                # so be careful to use the chord and the note in that case for
 550                # the appropriate operations.
 551                noteOrChord1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].general_note)  # type: ignore
 552                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:

 560                textExp.style.color = Visualization.DELETED_COLOR
 561                noteOrChord1.activeSite.insert(noteOrChord1.offset, textExp)
 562                continue

1561                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric offset")
1562                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1563                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1564                continue
1565
1566            if op[0] == "lyricstyleedit":
1567                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
1568                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
1569                # color the modified note (in both scores) using Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1570                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1571                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1572                    assert note1 is not None
1573                note1.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1574                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric style")
1575                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1576                note1.activeSite.insert(note1.offset, textExp)
1577
1578                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
1579                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1580                    assert note2 is not None
1581                note2.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1582                textExp = m21.expressions.TextExpression("changed lyric style")
1583                textExp.style.color = Visualization.CHANGED_COLOR
1584                note2.activeSite.insert(note2.offset, textExp)
1585                continue
1586
1587            print(
1588                f"Annotation type {op[0]} not yet supported for visualization",
1589                file=sys.stderr
1590            )

Mark up two music21 scores with the differences described by an operations list (e.g. a list returned from musicdiff.Comparison.annotated_scores_diff).

Arguments:
  • score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score to mark up
  • score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score to mark up
  • operations (list[tuple]): The operations list that describes the difference between the two scores
@staticmethod
def show_diffs( score1: music21.stream.base.Score, score2: music21.stream.base.Score, out_path1: str | pathlib.Path | None = None, out_path2: str | pathlib.Path | None = None) -> None: 
1592    @staticmethod
1593    def show_diffs(
1594        score1: m21.stream.Score,
1595        score2: m21.stream.Score,
1596        out_path1: str | Path | None = None,
1597        out_path2: str | Path | None = None
1598    ) -> None:
1599        """
1600        Render two (presumably marked-up) music21 scores.  If both out_path1 and
1601        out_path2 are not None, save the rendered PDFs at those two locations,
1602        otherwise just display them using the default PDF viewer on the system.
1603
1604        Args:
1605            score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score to render
1606            score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score to render
1607            out_path1 (str, Path): Where to save the first marked-up rendered score PDF.
1608                If out_path1 is None, both PDFs will be displayed in the default PDF viewer.
1609                (default is None)
1610            out_path2 (str, Path): Where to save the second marked-up rendered score PDF.
1611                If out_path2 is None, both PDFs will be displayed in the default PDF viewer.
1612                (default is None)
1613        """
1614        # display the two (presumably annotated) scores
1615        originalComposer1: str | None = None
1616        originalComposer2: str | None = None
1617
1618        if score1.metadata is None:
1619            score1.metadata = m21.metadata.Metadata()
1620        if score2.metadata is None:
1621            score2.metadata = m21.metadata.Metadata()
1622
1623        originalComposer1 = score1.metadata.composer
1624        if originalComposer1 is None:
1625            score1.metadata.composer = "score1"
1626        else:
1627            score1.metadata.composer = "score1          " + originalComposer1
1628
1629        originalComposer2 = score2.metadata.composer
1630        if originalComposer2 is None:
1631            score2.metadata.composer = "score2"
1632        else:
1633            score2.metadata.composer = "score2          " + originalComposer2
1634
1635        # save files if requested
1636        if (out_path1 is not None) and (out_path2 is not None):
1637            score1.write("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False, fp=out_path1)
1638            score2.write("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False, fp=out_path2)
1639            print(f"Annotated scores saved in {out_path1} and {out_path2}.", file=sys.stderr)
1640        else:
1641            # just display the scores
1642            score1.show("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False)
1643            score2.show("musicxml.pdf", makeNotation=False)

Render two (presumably marked-up) music21 scores. If both out_path1 and out_path2 are not None, save the rendered PDFs at those two locations, otherwise just display them using the default PDF viewer on the system.

Arguments:
  • score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score to render
  • score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score to render
  • out_path1 (str, Path): Where to save the first marked-up rendered score PDF. If out_path1 is None, both PDFs will be displayed in the default PDF viewer. (default is None)
  • out_path2 (str, Path): Where to save the second marked-up rendered score PDF. If out_path2 is None, both PDFs will be displayed in the default PDF viewer. (default is None)
@staticmethod
def get_text_output( score1: music21.stream.base.Score, score2: music21.stream.base.Score, operations: list[tuple], score1Name: str | pathlib.Path | None = None, score2Name: str | pathlib.Path | None = None) -> str: 
1742    @staticmethod
1743    def get_text_output(
1744        score1: m21.stream.Score,
1745        score2: m21.stream.Score,
1746        operations: list[tuple],
1747        score1Name: str | Path | None = None,
1748        score2Name: str | Path | None = None
1749    ) -> str:
1750        """
1751        Generate text output from the differences described by an operations list
1752        (e.g. a list returned from `musicdiff.Comparison.annotated_scores_diff`).
1753
1754        Args:
1755            score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score that was compared
1756            score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score that was compared
1757            operations (list[tuple]): The operations list that describes the difference
1758                between the two scores
1759            score1Name (str | Path | None): The name to use for the first score in the text output
1760            score2Name (str | Path | None): The name to use for the second score in the text output
1761        """
1762        output: str
1763        outputList: list[str] = []
1764        oneOutput: str  # one string, multiple lines (with \n at end of all but last line)
1765
1766        for op in operations:
1767            # bar
1768            if op[0] == "insbar":
1769                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMeasure)
1770                measure2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].measure)  # type: ignore
1771                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1772                    assert measure2 is not None
1773                newLine: str = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(measure2, score2)} @@\n"
1774                oneOutput = newLine
1775                newLine = f"+(measure) {op[2].readable_str()}"
1776                oneOutput += newLine
1777                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1778                continue
1779
1780            if op[0] == "delbar":
1781                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMeasure)
1782                measure1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].measure)  # type: ignore
1783                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1784                    assert measure1 is not None
1785                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(measure1, score1)} @@\n"
1786                oneOutput = newLine
1787                newLine = f"-(measure) {op[1].readable_str()}"
1788                oneOutput += newLine
1789                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1790                continue
1791
1792            # voices
1793            if op[0] == "voiceins":
1794                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnVoice)
1795                voice2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].voice)  # type: ignore
1796                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1797                    assert voice2 is not None
1798                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(voice2, score2)} @@\n"
1799                oneOutput = newLine
1800                newLine = f"+(voice) {op[2].readable_str()}"
1801                oneOutput += newLine
1802                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1803                continue
1804
1805            if op[0] == "voicedel":
1806                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnVoice)
1807                voice1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].voice)  # type: ignore
1808                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1809                    assert voice1 is not None
1810                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(voice1, score1)} @@\n"
1811                oneOutput = newLine
1812                newLine = f"-(voice) {op[1].readable_str()}"
1813                oneOutput += newLine
1814                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1815                continue
1816
1817            # extra
1818            if op[0] == "extrains":
1819                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1820                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1821                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1822                    assert extra2 is not None
1823                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra2, score2)} @@\n"
1824                oneOutput = newLine
1825                newLine = f"+({extra2.classes[0]}) {op[2].readable_str()}"
1826                oneOutput += newLine
1827                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1828                continue
1829
1830            if op[0] == "extradel":
1831                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1832                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
1833                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1834                    assert extra1 is not None
1835                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra1, score1)} @@\n"
1836                oneOutput = newLine
1837                newLine = f"-({extra1.classes[0]}) {op[1].readable_str()}"
1838                oneOutput += newLine
1839                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1840                continue
1841
1842            if op[0] == "extrasub":
1843                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1844                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1845                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
1846                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1847                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1848                    assert extra1 is not None
1849                    assert extra2 is not None
1850                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra1, score1)} @@\n"
1851                oneOutput = newLine
1852                newLine = f"-({extra1.classes[0]}) {op[1].readable_str()}"
1853                oneOutput += newLine
1854                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
1855                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
1856                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra2, score2)} @@\n"
1857                    oneOutput = newLine
1858                else:
1859                    oneOutput += "\n"
1860                newLine = f"+({extra2.classes[0]}) {op[2].readable_str()}"
1861                oneOutput += newLine
1862                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1863                continue
1864
1865            if op[0] == "extracontentedit":
1866                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1867                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1868                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
1869                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1870                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1871                    assert extra1 is not None
1872                    assert extra2 is not None
1873                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra1, score1)} @@\n"
1874                oneOutput = newLine
1875                newLine = f"-({extra1.classes[0]}:content) {op[1].readable_str('content')}"
1876                oneOutput += newLine
1877                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
1878                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
1879                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra2, score2)} @@\n"
1880                    oneOutput = newLine
1881                else:
1882                    oneOutput += "\n"
1883                newLine = f"+({extra2.classes[0]}:content) {op[2].readable_str('content')}"
1884                oneOutput += newLine
1885                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1886                continue
1887
1888            if op[0] == "extraoffsetedit":
1889                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1890                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1891                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
1892                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1893                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1894                    assert extra1 is not None
1895                    assert extra2 is not None
1896                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra1, score1)} @@\n"
1897                oneOutput = newLine
1898                newLine = f"-({extra1.classes[0]}:offset) {op[1].readable_str('offset')}"
1899                oneOutput += newLine

1903                oneOutput = newLine
1904                newLine = f"+({extra2.classes[0]}:offset) {op[2].readable_str('offset')}"
1905                oneOutput += newLine
1906                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1907                continue
1908
1909            if op[0] == "extradurationedit":
1910                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1911                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)

1913                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1914                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:

1924                    oneOutput = newLine
1925                else:
1926                    oneOutput += "\n"
1927                newLine = f"+({extra2.classes[0]}:dur) {op[2].readable_str('duration')}"

1929                outputList.append(oneOutput)

1931
1932            if op[0] == "extrastyleedit":
1933                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnExtra)
1934                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnExtra)
1935                sd1 = op[1].styledict
1936                sd2 = op[2].styledict
1937                changedStr = ""
1938                for k1, v1 in sd1.items():
1939                    if k1 not in sd2 or sd2[k1] != v1:
1940                        if changedStr:
1941                            changedStr += ","
1942                        changedStr += k1
1943
1944                # one last thing: check for keys in sd2 that aren't in sd1
1945                for k2 in sd2:
1946                    if k2 not in sd1:
1947                        if changedStr:
1948                            changedStr += ","
1949                        changedStr += k2
1950
1951                extra1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].extra)  # type: ignore
1952                extra2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].extra)  # type: ignore
1953                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
1954                    assert extra1 is not None
1955                    assert extra2 is not None
1956                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra1, score1)} @@\n"
1957                oneOutput = newLine
1958                style1: str = op[1].readable_str('style', changedStr=changedStr)
1959                style2: str = op[2].readable_str('style', changedStr=changedStr)
1960                newLine = f"-({extra1.classes[0]}:{changedStr}) {style1}"
1961                oneOutput += newLine
1962                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
1963                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
1964                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(extra2, score2)} @@\n"
1965                    oneOutput = newLine
1966                else:
1967                    oneOutput += "\n"

1969                oneOutput += newLine
1970                outputList.append(oneOutput)
1971                continue
1972

2673                    assert note1 is not None
2674                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2675                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2676                    assert note2 is not None
2677                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note1, score1)} @@\n"
2678                oneOutput = newLine
2679                newLine = f"-(Lyric:number) {op[1].readable_str('number')}"
2680                oneOutput += newLine
2681                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
2682                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
2683                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note2, score2)} @@\n"
2684                    oneOutput = newLine
2685                else:
2686                    oneOutput += "\n"
2687                newLine = f"+(Lyric:number) {op[2].readable_str('number')}"
2688                oneOutput += newLine
2689                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2690                continue
2691
2692            if op[0] == "lyricidedit":
2693                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
2694                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
2695                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2696                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2697                    assert note1 is not None
2698                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2699                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2700                    assert note2 is not None
2701                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note1, score1)} @@\n"
2702                oneOutput = newLine
2703                newLine = f"-(Lyric:id) {op[1].readable_str('id')}"
2704                oneOutput += newLine
2705                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
2706                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
2707                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note2, score2)} @@\n"
2708                    oneOutput = newLine
2709                else:
2710                    oneOutput += "\n"
2711                newLine = f"+(Lyric:id) {op[2].readable_str('id')}"
2712                oneOutput += newLine
2713                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2714                continue
2715
2716            if op[0] == "lyricoffsetedit":
2717                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
2718                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
2719                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2720                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2721                    assert note1 is not None
2722                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2723                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2724                    assert note2 is not None
2725                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note1, score1)} @@\n"
2726                oneOutput = newLine
2727                newLine = f"-(Lyric:offset) {op[1].readable_str('offset')}\n"
2728                oneOutput += newLine
2729                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note2, score2)} @@\n"
2730                oneOutput += newLine
2731                newLine = f"+(Lyric:offset) {op[2].readable_str('offset')}"
2732                oneOutput += newLine
2733                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2734                continue
2735
2736            if op[0] == "lyricstyleedit":
2737                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnLyric)
2738                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnLyric)
2739                note1 = score1.recurse().getElementById(op[1].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2740                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2741                    assert note1 is not None
2742                note2 = score2.recurse().getElementById(op[2].lyric_holder)  # type: ignore
2743                if t.TYPE_CHECKING:
2744                    assert note2 is not None
2745                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note1, score1)} @@\n"
2746                oneOutput = newLine
2747                newLine = f"-(Lyric:style) {op[1].readable_str('style')}"
2748                oneOutput += newLine
2749                if op[1].offset != op[2].offset:
2750                    outputList.append(oneOutput)
2751                    newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(note2, score2)} @@\n"
2752                    oneOutput = newLine
2753                else:
2754                    oneOutput += "\n"
2755                newLine = f"+(Lyric:style) {op[2].readable_str('style')}"
2756                oneOutput += newLine
2757                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2758                continue
2759
2760            # metadata
2761            if op[0] == "mditemins":
2762                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMetadataItem)
2763                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(score1.metadata, score1)} @@\n"
2764                oneOutput = newLine
2765                newLine = f"+(metadata) {op[1].readable_str()}"
2766                oneOutput += newLine
2767                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2768                continue
2769
2770            if op[0] == "mditemdel":
2771                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMetadataItem)
2772                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(score1.metadata, score1)} @@\n"
2773                oneOutput = newLine
2774                newLine = f"-(metadata) {op[1].readable_str()}"
2775                oneOutput += newLine
2776                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2777                continue
2778
2779            if op[0] == "mditemsub":
2780                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMetadataItem)
2781                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMetadataItem)
2782                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(score1.metadata, score1)} @@\n"
2783                oneOutput = newLine
2784                newLine = f"-(metadata) {op[1].readable_str()}\n"
2785                oneOutput += newLine
2786                newLine = f"+(metadata) {op[2].readable_str()}"
2787                oneOutput += newLine
2788                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2789                continue
2790
2791            if op[0] == "mditemkeyedit":
2792                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMetadataItem)
2793                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMetadataItem)
2794                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(score1.metadata, score1)} @@\n"
2795                oneOutput = newLine
2796                newLine = f"-(metadata:key) {op[1].readable_str()}\n"
2797                oneOutput += newLine
2798                newLine = f"+(metadata:key) {op[2].readable_str()}"
2799                oneOutput += newLine
2800                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2801                continue
2802
2803            if op[0] == "mditemvalueedit":
2804                assert isinstance(op[1], AnnMetadataItem)
2805                assert isinstance(op[2], AnnMetadataItem)
2806                newLine = f"@@ {Visualization._location_of(score1.metadata, score1)} @@\n"
2807                oneOutput = newLine
2808                newLine = f"-(metadata:value) {op[1].readable_str()}\n"
2809                oneOutput += newLine
2810                newLine = f"+(metadata:value) {op[2].readable_str()}"
2811                oneOutput += newLine
2812                outputList.append(oneOutput)
2813                continue
2814
2815            print(
2816                f"Annotation type {op[0]} not yet supported for visualization",
2817                file=sys.stderr
2818            )
2819
2820        # Sort by measure number (int), then measure number suffix (str), then part
2821        # number, and then beat (as parsed from "@@ measure 3b, staff 2, beat 1.5 @@")
2822        # The goal is for all measure 0's to be printed first (with measure 0's staff 0
2823        # first), with the contents of each staff of each measure coming out in beat order.
2824        LOC_PATTERN: str = (
2825            r"\@\@ measure (\d+)(\w*), staff (\d+), beat (\d+|\d+[./]\d+|\d+ \d+/\d+) \@\@"
2826        )
2827        def measNum(s: str) -> int:
2828            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2829            if not m:
2830                return -1
2831            measNumStr: str = m.group(1)
2832            measNum: int = -1
2833            try:
2834                measNum = int(measNumStr)
2835            except Exception:
2836                pass
2837            return measNum
2838
2839        def measSuf(s: str) -> str:
2840            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2841            if not m:
2842                return ''
2843            measSuf: str = m.group(2)
2844            return measSuf
2845
2846        def staffNum(s: str) -> int:
2847            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2848            if not m:
2849                return -1
2850            staffNumStr: str = m.group(3)
2851            staffNum: int = -1
2852            try:
2853                staffNum = int(staffNumStr)
2854            except Exception:
2855                pass
2856            return staffNum
2857
2858        def beat(s: str) -> OffsetQL:
2859            # can be of the form "j n/m" (mixed), "n/m" (Fraction), or "n.m" (float)
2860            m = re.match(LOC_PATTERN, s)
2861            if not m:
2862                return 0.
2863            beatStr: str = m.group(4)
2864            beats: OffsetQL = 0.
2865            beatsFrac: Fraction = Fraction(0, 1)
2866            beatsFloat: float = 0.
2867            try:
2868                if " " in beatStr and "/" in beatStr:
2869                    # mixed fraction "j n/m"
2870                    nums: list[str] = beatStr.split(' ')
2871                    wholeNum: int = int(nums[0])
2872                    frac: Fraction = Fraction(nums[1])
2873                    beats = opFrac(wholeNum + frac)
2874                elif "/" in beatStr:
2875                    # fraction
2876                    beatsFrac = Fraction(beatStr)
2877                    beats = opFrac(beatsFrac)
2878                else:
2879                    beatsFloat = float(beatStr)
2880                    beats = opFrac(beatsFloat)
2881            except Exception:
2882                pass
2883            return beats
2884
2885        outputList.sort(key=lambda s: (measNum(s), measSuf(s), staffNum(s), beat(s)))
2886
2887        if operations:
2888            # filenames only show up at the start of text output if there are any diffs
2889            if score1Name:
2890                outputList.insert(0, f"--- {score1Name}")
2891                outputList.insert(1, f"+++ {score2Name}")
2892            else:
2893                outputList.insert(0, "--- score1")
2894                outputList.insert(1, "+++ score2")
2895
2896        output = '\n'.join(outputList)
2897        return output

Generate text output from the differences described by an operations list (e.g. a list returned from musicdiff.Comparison.annotated_scores_diff).

Arguments:
  • score1 (music21.stream.Score): The first score that was compared
  • score2 (music21.stream.Score): The second score that was compared
  • operations (list[tuple]): The operations list that describes the difference between the two scores
  • score1Name (str | Path | None): The name to use for the first score in the text output
  • score2Name (str | Path | None): The name to use for the second score in the text output
